<EFX_PART_I>
<A NAME="FIS_PART_I"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT -36PT 0PT 0PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	PART I
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT -36PT 0PT 18PT;TEXT-INDENT: -18PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<EFX_BUSINESS>
<A NAME="FIS_BUSINESS"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT -36PT 6PT 18PT;TEXT-INDENT: -18PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<A NAME="ARIS-20160731X10K_HTM_ITEM_1">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Item&nbsp;1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Business
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Overview
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	ARI Network Services, Inc. offers
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	an award-winning suite of Lead G
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	eneration and eCommerce Websites, eCatalog Solutions, Business Management Systems and Digital Marketing Services that help dealers, equipment&nbsp;manufacturers and distributors in select vertical markets Sell More Stuff!&#x2122;&nbsp;&#x2013; online and in-store. Our innovative products are powered by a proprietary library of enriched electronic product content including OEM parts, aftermarket parts, garments and accessories (PG&amp;A) and whole goods from more
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	than 1,800 manufacturers. Business is complicated, but we believe our customers&#x2019; technology tools don&#x2019;t have to be. We&nbsp;remove the complexity of selling and servicing new and used whole goods inventory and PG&amp;A. More than 23,500 equipm
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	ent dealers, distributors and manufacturers worldwide leverage our solutions to Sell More Stuff!&#x2122;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	We go to market under the &#x201C;ARI Network Services, Inc.&#x201D; brand name in the powersports, outdoor power equipment (OPE), marine, home medical equipment (HME), recreational vehicles (RV) and appliance industries. We service customers in the automotive tire and wheel aftermarket (ATW) under the &#x201C;TCS Technologies, an ARI Company&#x201D; brand name; and we service the automotive aftermarket parts and service (AAPS) market under the &#x201C;DCi, an ARI Company&#x201D; brand name.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	We were incorporated in Wisconsin in 1981. Our principal executive office and headquarters is located in Milwaukee, Wisconsin
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	The office address is 10850 West Park Place, Suite 1200, Milwaukee, WI 53224, and our telephone number at that location is (414) 973-4300. Our principal website address is
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	www.arinet.com
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. ARI also maintains operations in Cypress, California; Floyds Knobs, Indiana; Des Moines, Iowa; Duluth, Minnesota; Wexford, Pennsylvania; Cookeville, Tennessee;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	Salt Lake City, Utah;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Leiden, The Netherlands and Gurgaon, India.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Our Solutions
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Our primary solutions include: (i)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Lead Generation and eCommerce Websites,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	giving
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	dealers and wholesalers
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	an online
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	presence optimized for today&#x2019;s digital path to purchase and serving as a platform to drive in-bound lead generation and eCommerce sales; (ii)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	eCatalogs
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	, offer
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	ing
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	access to our proprietary library of enriched electronic product content via a suite of SaaS and DaaS solutions to enable the sale of whole goods inventory and PG&amp;A; (iii)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	B
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	usiness Management
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&nbsp;S
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	oftware
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	designed to streamline every aspect of a dealer&#x2019;s operation, drive profitability and allow them to provide better customer service; and (iv)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	D
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	igita
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	l M
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	arketing
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	S
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	ervice
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	designed to generate leads and drive traffic both to the dealer&#x2019;s website and brick-and-mortar location.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

	Our solutions also improve our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	dealer
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	s&#x2019; overall customer satisfaction through a highly efficient and accurate data lookup experience at the parts counter and a quicker response time to online inquiries, both of which serve to significantly improve a customer&#x2019;s overall experience with the dealer.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	&#xFEFF;

	Our solutions are sold through our internal sales force and are composed primarily of recurring licenses and subscriptions and, in the case of business management software, perpetual licenses and maintenance contracts. Customers typically sign annual, auto-renewing contracts. Today, more than 90% of our revenues are recurring.

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	These strategic foundations are primarily centered on enhancing the value proposition to our customers, which will lead to additional revenues through pricing actions, product and feature upsells, reduced customer churn rates, and expansion by leveraging our core competencies in new complementary markets. Each of these strategic pillars is a long-term foundation for the Company&#x2019;s growth; within each we have established near-term goals, as discussed below.
</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	As a subscription-based, recurring revenue (RR) business, the most important drivers of future growth are nurturing and defending our customer base; developing and selling additional products to our existing customer base; and acquiring new customers. We define RR as revenue from products and services which are subscription-based and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	renewable, including software access fees, data content fees, maintenance fees, support fees and hosting fees. We define churn as the percentage of RR that does not renew. RR increased
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	20
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	.

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	%, or $
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	7
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	428
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	,000 to 92.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	% of total revenue for the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	year
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	ended
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	July 31
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	, 2016, compar
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	ed to the same period last year
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	. To experience further gro
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	wth in RR, we will continue to

The introduction of new solutions, upgrades to existing products, and new feature sets are all designed to grow
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	PG&amp;A Content Addition and Expansion &#x2013; We&#x2019;ve released two new powersports catalogs, adding more than 35,000 new products available to the market.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;

<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Enter new markets.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	ARI currently maintains a significant share in our core vertical markets of OPE, powersports, marine, RV and appliances. Accordingly, we anticipate low single-digit growth in these markets. ARI maintains a lower share in our growth vertical markets of HME, ATW and AAPS. Accordingly, we anticipate double-digit growth in these markets.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	As we continue to increase our share in our current markets, leveraging our technology in new and underserved markets will be important to maintaining
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	high single digit to low double digit
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	organic growth rates. ARI currently has more than 3,000 dealer websites in the ATW market. We estimate that the total addressable market includes approximately 18,000 dealers. Further, the broader AAPS market, which we entered via our acquisition of DCi, comprises nearly 80,000 independent service providers, more than all of our other markets combined. We intend to continue to invest heavily in this growth market, including seeking opportunities to leverage our products and services in the broader AAPS. We are one of the first website providers to service the HME market. We estimate that this market comprises nearly 25,000 service providers and believe the market to be in the early stages of eCommerce adoption.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	E
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	xpand geographically
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	Although we maintain relationships with dealers throughout the world, we have low penetration into international markets. Growing our international business will require us to secure and publish electronic content from manufacturers outside the U.S. and make changes to our existing product suite that will allow us to rapidly deploy these products in a scalable and efficient manner without the need to have &#x201C;boots on the ground&#x201D; in those countries
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	During fiscal 2015 and 2016, we added 15 new catalog content offerings in the international outdoor power equipment market.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	In September 2016, we hired a general manager in the Netherlands
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	intended
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	to expand our European presence.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Nurture and retain existing customers through world-class customer service and value-added product feature updates.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	In order to achieve sustained double-digit organic growth, we not only need to execute the growth strategies described above, we must also retain our existing customers. In a SaaS business, the cost to retain an existing customer is much less than the cost to acquire a new customer. Accordingly, customer churn is an important metric we track and manage. We experienced improvements in our churn rates the past several years as a result of strategic actions taken by the Company, all of which are designed to enhance the &#x201C;stickiness&#x201D; of our product within our customers&#x2019; operations. In fiscal 2016, we experienced a slight decrease in customer churn from 15.5% in fiscal 2015 to 15.4%. We will continue to leverage our relationships with existing customers and closely monitor and manage the level of customer churn.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Lead the market with open integration to related platforms.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	One of our strategic advantages is our focus on integrating our solutions with dealer business management systems (DMS) in order to pass key information, including customer and transactional data, between our solutions and the DMS, saving our customers valuable time and eliminating redundant data entry. We currently have integration capabilities with over 90 DMS (we refer to these
</FONT>

	relationships as &#x201C;Compass Partners&#x201D;), and we continue to seek other strategic alliances that can be integrated with our product and service offerings.

</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Successfully execute acquisitions that align with our core strategy.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	S
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	ince 1995, we have had a formal corporate development program aimed at identifying, evaluating and closing acquisitions that align with our strategy. We focus on vertically-oriented markets with a large base of independent, multi-line dealers that sell and service complex equipment. Our strategy is to acquire companies that allow us to do one or more of the following: (i) expand our market share in existing verticals; (ii) expand into new markets that fit our desired profile; (iii) provide us with complementary products which can be cross-sold to our existing customer base; (iv) provide opportunities to cross-sell our existing products; and (v) can be integrated into our operations, thereby creating cost-saving synergies.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	From the program&#x2019;s inception through the end of fiscal 2016, we have closed 16 acquisitions. A summary of some of our most recent acquisitions is as follows:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	Our acquisition of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	Tire Company Solutions, LLC (&#x201C;T
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	CS
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x201D;)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	not only cemented our position as one of the largest suppliers of eCommerce solutions in the ATW market, but also added a new business management software product to the Company&#x2019;s product suite for retailers, wholesalers and retreaders in the ATW and AAPS markets.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">

<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;FONT-FAMILY:SYMBOL;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;FONT-SIZE:10PT;;">
	&#xB7;

<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:12PT 0PT 0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	Our acquisition of TASCO
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	Corporation (&#x201C;TASCO&#x201D;)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	has extended our position as a business management system leader in the ATW market, including the addition of business management software dedicated to solving the unique needs of large, multi-location franchised businesses.

<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">

<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:18PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:18PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 17.00PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:SYMBOL;FONT-SIZE:10PT;;">
	&#xB7;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:1PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:1PT;WIDTH:1PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	Our acquisition of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	Direct Communications Inc. (&#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	DCi
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#x201D;)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	accelerated our entry into the AAPS market. DCi is a leading provider of differentiated product content and electronic parts catalog software serving manuf
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	acturers, distributors, jobbers
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	and independent retailers in the AAPS.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	Our Competitive Strengths
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Market Leader in Core Verticals
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	We believe that we are one of the leaders in each of our core vertical markets. More than 23,500 equipment dealers, distributors and manufacturers worldwide leverage our web and eCatalog
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	platforms, allowing us to cost
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	effectively leverage our proprietary library of enriched electronic product content into a larg
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	e and diversified customer base
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	and to launch new product enhancements and technology-enabled solutions into the vertical markets we serve.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Breadth and Depth of Published Content
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	The breadth and depth of our content library, as well as our ability to enhance and efficiently publish manufacturers&#x2019; data as it becomes available, provides ARI with a critical competitive advantage and represents a high barrier to entry for potential new competitors. Our content library enables multi-line dealers to easily access catalog content for multiple manufacturers using a single software platform. This advantage, which saves our customers significant time, provides "stickiness" for our catalog customer base which allows us to efficiently and cost effectively nurture our existing customers while devoting resources to develop new products and services, enabling us to grow our overall
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	dealer subscriber
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	base as well as ARPD.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
</P>
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;PUNCTUATION-WRAP:HANGING;VERTICAL-ALIGN:BASELINE;FONT-FAMILY:CG TIMES (W1);FONT-SIZE: 8PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
	9
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<HR SIZE="3" STYLE="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<P STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage10"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Recurring Revenue Model
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	During fiscal 2016, more than 90% of our revenue was subscription-based and RR. The majority of our customers are on contracts of 12 months or longer, and these contracts typically auto-renew for additional 12-month terms. This provides us with advanced visibility into our future revenues and opportunities to sell additional services to our customers. Our RR model also emphasizes the importance of maintaining a low rate of customer churn, one of the key financial drivers of any SaaS business. We closely
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	monitor customer churn via end-of-
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	service surveys, so we can take action on the churn drivers within our control in order to reduce churn rates in the future.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Our RR model, when combined with low rates of customer churn, significantly reduces the cost to maintain and nurture our customer base. This, in turn, frees up resources to enhance our existing products and work toward new revenue
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	-
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	generating product innovations. Additionally, a substantial portion of our eCatalog business is focused on our customers&#x2019; service and repair operations. This allows our revenues to remain strong even in a down economy, as consumers tend to repair their equipment rather than buy new equipment during challenging economic times.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Suite of Products Covers Entire Sales and Service Cycle
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Our suite of dealer products and services enhance our customers' front office operations by covering the entire sales cycle from lead generation and lead management to eCommerce sales of whole goods and PG&amp;A to billing and collections. Additionally, our eCatalog products, website service scheduling features and customer relationship management functionality in our business management systems allow dealers to efficiently service and repair their customer&#x2019;s existing equipment to build their customer&#x2019;s lifetime value.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	We believe that our competitive advantages will enable us to compete effectively and sustainably in our vertical markets, although given the current pace of technological change, it is possible that as yet unidentified competitors could emerge; existing competitors could merge and/or obtain additional capital, thereby making them more formidable; or new technologies could come on-stream and potentially threaten our position.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Our Markets and the Challenges We Face
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Competition for our products and services varies by product and by vertical market. We believe that no single competitor today offers a product and service portfolio that competes against all of our offerings in any of our vertical markets.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	In the eCatalogs product category, we compete primarily with Snap-on Business Solutions which designs and delivers eCatalogs, accessory sales tools and manufacturer network development services primarily to the automotive, powersports and OPE markets. In addition, there are a variety of smaller eCatalog companies
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	each
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	focused on one to two vertical markets.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	In the lead management, dealer websites and eCommerce product category, our primary competitors in powersports and marine are Dealer Spike and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	PowerSports Network, owned by Dominion Enterprises. We also compete with Net Driven in the ATW market. Competition for our website development services also comes from
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	dealers&#x2019;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	in-house information technology groups that may prefer to build their own web-based proprietary systems, rather than utilizing our proven industry solutions.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	There are also large, general market eCommerce companies, such as IBM, which offer products and services that could address some of our customers&#x2019; needs. These general eCommerce companies do not typically compete with us directly, but they could in the future.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	We believe we maintain a competitive advantage in our core vertical markets given the breadth and integration of our published catalog content into our eCatalog and website products.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Several of the markets we serve, including powersports, marine and RV, are closely aligned with the state of the economy, given the luxury nature of the products in those verticals. Our customer churn rates have shown improvement in these markets over the past several fiscal years. However, future economic downturns could have a significant
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	adverse
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	impact on our business
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	as a downturn could lead to an increase in customer churn in these markets due to manufacturer bankruptcies, dealer closures and extreme cost reduction measures by our dealer customers. It is also important to note that the effects of a difficult economic environment may be somewhat softened, relative to other product and service providers to the markets, by the consumers' willingness in a down economy to repair existing equipment rather than purchase new equipment
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	This
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	serves to amplify the importance of our published OEM replacement parts and PG&amp;A content provided to customers via our eCatalog products and our dealer websites.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
</P>
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Intellectual Property
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	We rely on various intellectual property laws in the United States and other jurisdictions as well as confidentiality procedures and contractual provisions to protect our proprietary technology and our brand. We also enter into confidentiality and proprietary rights agreements with our employees, consultants and other third parties, and we control access to software, documentation and other proprietary information. We have numerous registered trademarks in the U.S. and Europe.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Employees
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	As of July 31, 2016, we had 4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	05
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	full-time equivalent employees (FTEs) and a total of 415 employees. Of these FTEs, 19

	4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	are involved in customer operations and support; 11
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	are in sales and marketing; 6

	6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	are engaged in maintaining or developing software and providing software customization services; and 3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	are involved in general and administrative functions. None of these employees are represented by a union.

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Fiscal Year
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	ARI&#x2019;s fiscal year ends on July 31

	. Any references throughout this document to &#x201C;2016&#x201D; or &#x201C;fiscal 2016&#x201D; and &#x201C;2015&#x201D; or &#x201C;fiscal 2015&#x201D; refer to the fiscal years ended July 31, 2016, and July 31, 2015, respectively.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<EFX_NAME_AND_TITLE>
<A NAME="FIS_NAME_AND_TITLE"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Executive
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Team
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	The table below sets forth the names of ARI&#x2019;s executive team as of October 21, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	The executives serve at the discretion of the Board of Directors.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	&#xFEFF;

</EFX_NAME_AND_TITLE>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Roy W. Olivier
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Olivier was appointed President and Chief Executive Officer of the Company in May 2008, after having served in the capacity of Vice President of Global Sales and Marketing of the Company since September 2006. Prior to joining ARI in 2006, Olivier was a consultant to start-up, small
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	-
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	and medium-sized businesses. Prior to that, he served as Vice President of Sales and Marketing for ProQuest Media Solutions, a business he founded in 1993 and sold to ProQuest in 2000. Olivier previously held various sales and marketing executive and managerial positions with several other companies in the telecommunications and computer industries, including Multicom Publishing Inc., Tandy Corporation, BusinessLand and PacTel.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#7F7C7D;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#7F7C7D;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	William A. Nurthen
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Nurthen was appointed Vice President of Finance and Chief Financial Officer of ARI in November 2013 when he joined the Company. Nurthen also serves as Treasurer and Corporate Secretary. Prior to joining ARI, Nurthen served as CFO of Cabrera Capital Markets, LLC, an investment banking firm from 2011 to 2013. Prior to that, he served in a variety of high-level financial leadership positions including CFO of bioLytical Laboratories from 2008 to 2011. From 1999 to 2007, Nurthen served in various financial roles at Inforte Corp., a NASDAQ company, including Vice President of Finance and CFO
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	From 1997 to 1999, Nurthen worked in various financial operations roles at Platinum Technology International, Inc., a software and consulting company. Nurthen earned his B.A. from The University of Notre Dame in 1995 and his MBA from The Kellogg School of Management at Northwestern University in 2002.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Robert A. Ostermann
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF;">
	Ostermann was appointed Chief Technology Officer of ARI in August 2012 after having served as Executive Director of Technology s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF;">
	ince
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF;">
	November 2011
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF;">
	Prior to that, he served as Director of Product Engineering since joining the Company in June 2008. Before joining ARI, Ostermann served in various technology management and development roles at Parcel Pro Inc. in Torrance, California, and The California Breath Clinics in Los Angeles, California from 2003 to 2008. Prior to that, he was lead developer at OC-Net, Inc., a company ARI acquired in January 2008, in Cypress, California. Ostermann earned a B.S. in Business Administration, Computer Information Systems from California State University.
</FONT>
</P>

</EFX_BUSINESS>
<EFX_RISK_FACTORS>
<A NAME="FIS_RISK_FACTORS"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<A NAME="ARIS-20160731X10K_HTM_ITEM_1A">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Item&nbsp;1A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	. Risk Factors
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	The risks and uncertainties described below are not the only ones the Company faces. Other events that we do not currently anticipate or that we do not currently deem to be material also affect our results of operations and financial condition.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Continued uncertain economic conditions or reduced investments in technology spending may negatively impact our business.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Our business depends on the overall demand for technology services spending and on the economic health and general willingness of our current and prospective customers to make capital and expense commitments. If the conditions in the U.S. and global economic environment remain uncertain or continue to be volatile, or if they deteriorate further, our business, operating results, and financial condition may be adversely affected. Our customers sell capital goods, some of which are considered luxury in nature, which are highly dependent on the disposable income of end consumers. Weak or volatile economic conditions or a reduction in consumer spending may weaken our customers&#x2019; demand for eCatalogs, lead management and eCommerce websites, business management software
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	, digital marketing services
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	and other technology-enabled services or their general information technology spending, which would likely harm our business and operating results in a number of ways
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	including longer sales cycles, potential lower prices for our services, reduced sales and increased churn.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	We may become liable to our customers and lose customers if we have defects or disruptions in our service or if we provide poor service.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Because we deliver some of our technology as a service, errors or defects in the software appli
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	cations underlying our services
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	or a failur
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	e of our hosting infrastructure
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	may make our services, in particular our eCommerce services, unavailable to our customers. Since our customers use our eCommerce services to facilitate their sales, any errors,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	defects, disruptions in service
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	or other performance problems with our services, whether in connection with the day-to-day operation of our services, upgrades or otherwise, could damage our customers&#x2019; businesses.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Despite the implementation of security measures, the core of our network infrastructure is vulnerable to unauthorized access, computer viruses, equipment failure and other disruptive problems including the following:
</FONT>
</P>

	&nbsp;

<A NAME="eolPage13"></A>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:18PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:18PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 17.00PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;FONT-FAMILY:SYMBOL;FONT-SIZE:8PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;;">
	&#xB7;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:1PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:1PT;WIDTH:1PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	eliminating computer viruses and alleviating other security or technical problems may require interruptions, delays or cessation of service to our customers.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	If we have any errors, defects, disruptions in service or other performance problems with our services, customers could elect not to renew,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	customers could
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	delay or withhold payment to us, we could lo
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	se future sales or customers could
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	make claims against us which could result in an increase in our provision for doubtful accounts, an increase in collection cycles for accounts receivable or litigation costs.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	We may be exposed to risks and costs associated with protecting the integrity and security of our customers&#x2019; information.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	A significant number of customers make purchases from us using credit cards. In order for our business to function successfully, we and other market participants must be able to handle and transmit confidential
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	information, including credit card information, securely.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	T
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	here can be no assurance that in the future we will be able to operate our facilities and our customer service and sales operations in accordance with PCI or other industry recommended practices.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	Further, there is increased litigation over personally identifiable information, and we may be subject to one or more claims or lawsuits related to intentional or unintentional exposure of our customer&#x2019;s personally identifiable information. Even if we are compliant with PCI standards, we still may not be able to prevent security breaches involving customer transaction data. Any breach could cause consumers to lose confidence in the security of our websites and choose not to purchase from us. If a computer hacker or other criminal is able to circumvent our security measures, he or she could destroy or steal valuable information or disrupt our operations. Any security breach could expose us to risks of data loss, fines, litigation and liability, and could seriously disrupt our operations and harm our reputation, any of which could adversely affect our business.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	In addition, states and the federal government have enacted additional laws and regulations to protect consumers against identity theft, including laws governing treatment of personally identifiable information. We collect and store personal information from consumers in the course of doing business. These laws have increased the costs of doing business, and if we fail to implement appropriate safeguards, or we fail to detect and provide prompt notice of unauthorized access as required by some of these laws, we could be subject to potential claims for damages and other remedies. If we were required to pay any significant amounts in satisfaction of claims under these laws, or if we were forced to cease our business operations for any length of time as a result of our inability to comply fully with any such law, our business, operating results and financial condition could be adversely affected.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Our core markets and verticals are competitive, and if we do not compete effectively, our operating results may be negatively impacted.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	The markets for eCatalogs, lead management and eCommerce websites, business management software
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	, digital marketing services
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	and other technology-enabled services targeted at our vertical markets are comp
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	etitive, and the eCommerce area
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	specifically, is rapidly changing with relatively low barriers to entry. With the introduction of new technologies and market entrants, we expect competition to remain intense. In addition, increased competition generally could result in reduced sales, reduced margin or the failure of our services to achieve or maintain more widespread market acceptance. Competition in our market is based principally upon service breadth and functionality; service performance, security and reliability; the ability to tailor and customize services for a specific company, vertical market or industry; ease of use of the service; speed and ease of deployment, integration and configuration; total cost of ownership, including price, implementation costs and support costs; professional services implementation; strength of customer relationships; and financial resources of the vendor. To compete effectively, we also must be able to more frequently update our services to meet market demand.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	Our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	larger
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	principal competitors include Snap-on Business Solutions and PowerSports Network, owned by Dominion Enterprises. Some of our actual and potential competitors enjoy competitive advantages over us such as greater name recognition within our target vertical markets, larger marketing budgets as well as substantially greater financial, technical and other resources. If we are not able to compete effectively, our operating results will be harmed.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	The impact of negative factors on the business may not be immediately reflected in our financial results.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	Because we recognize subscription revenue over the term of the applicable agreement, non-renewal of subscriptions or reductions in new service agreements may not be immediately reflected in our operating results. The majority of our revenue in any given period is attributable to service agreements entered into during previous periods. A decline in new or renewed service agreements in any one period will not be fully reflected in our revenue in that period, but will reduce our revenue in future periods. As a result, the effect of significant downturns in sales and market acceptance of our services in a particular period may not be fully reflected in our operating results until future periods. Our subscription model also makes it difficult for us to rapidly increase our revenue through additional sales in any period because revenue from new customers must be recognized over the applicable subscription term.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
</P>
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>

	Our operating results may fluctuate from quarter to quarter.

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	We expect that a portion of our revenue in the future will be derived from non-recurring fee income, which consists primarily of revenues from professional services such as software customization and training, software sales and one-time network installation fees. The timing of recording of this revenue is dependent upon several factors that we cannot predict. These factors include:

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	Our costs are not entirely predictable and may vary from quarter-to-quarter due to acquisitions or non-recurring expenditures. Cash flows may also vary from quarter to quarter, depending on the timing of disbursements and customer payments. These fluctuations may make period-to-period comparisons of our results of operations more complex.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Changes in financial accounting standards or practices may cause adverse, unexpected financial reporting fluctuations and harm our operating results.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	A change in accounting standards or practices could harm our operating results and may even affect our reporting of transactions completed before the change is effective. New accounting pronouncements and varying interpretations of accounting pronouncements have occurred and may occur in the future. Changes to existing rules or the questioning of current practices may harm our operating results or the way we conduct our business and may increase our compliance costs.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Our business could suffer if we are unable to protect our intellectual property rights or become liable for infringing
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	on
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	the intellectual property rights of others.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	We regard our trademarks, proprietary technology and similar intellectual property as critical to our success, and we rely upon trademark law, trade secret protection and confidentiality and license agreements with our employees, strategic partners and others to protect our proprietary rights, but these measures can have only limited effectiveness. Prevalent use of the Internet has also increased the ease with which third parties can distribute our intellectual property without our authorization.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	We intend to pursue the registration of our material trademarks as necessary. We may not be entitled to the benefits of any such registration until such registration takes effect. In addition, effective protection may not be available in every country in which our products are available. Further, we may be subject to claims in the ordinary course of our business, including claims of alleged infringement of the trademarks, copyrights and other intellectual property rights of third parties by us and our licensees.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	Other parties may assert claims of infringement of intellectual property or other proprietary rights against us. These claims, even if without merit, could require us to expend significant financial and managerial resources. Furthermore, if claims like this were successful, we might be required to change our trademarks, alter our content, products or services, or pay financial damages, any of which could substantially increase our operating expenses. We also may be required to obtain licenses from others to refine, develop, market and deliver new services. We may be unable to obtain any needed license on commercially reasonable terms or at all, and rights granted under any licenses may not be valid and enforceable. In the future, we could be subject to legal proceedings and claims from time to time in the ordinary course of our business, including claims of alleged infringement of trademarks and other intellectual property rights of third parties by us and our licensees. Any such claims could have a material adverse effect on our business, financial condition and operating results.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	We are dependent on our management and employees.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	We are dependent on the services of our executive officers and other key employees. There can be no assurance, however, that we can obtain executives of comparable expertise and commitment in the event of death, disability or voluntary departure of one of our executive officers or other key employees, or that our business would not suffer material adverse effects as the result of the death, disability or voluntary departure. Further, the loss of the services of any one or more of these employees could have an adverse effect on our business. In addition, we will also need to attract and retain other highly skilled technical and managerial personnel for whom competition is intense. If we are unable to do so, our business, results of operations and financial condition could be materially and adversely affected.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

<A NAME="eolPage15"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Our common stock has had limited trading.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Trading in our common stock has historically been thin. Because of the thinness of the market for our stock, the price of our common stock may be subject to manipulation. This limited trading may adversely affect the liquidity of our common stock, not only in terms of the number of shares that can be bought and sold at a given price, but also through delays in the timing of transactions and reduction in security analysts&#x2019; and the media&#x2019;s coverage of us. As a result, there could be a larger spread between the bid and the ask prices of our common stock and investors may not be able to sell shares of our common stock when or at prices they desire.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	We may not be able to identify, acquire and successfully integrate acquisitions.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	A key component of our growth strategy has been and will continue to be acquisitions and other business development opportunities that solidify or accelerate our market position in our core offerings and vertical markets. The successful implementation of this strategy depends upon our ability to identify suitable acquisition candidates, acquire such businesses on acceptable terms, finance the acquisitions and integrate their operations successfully into ARI. There can be no assurance that such candidates will be available or, if such candidates are available, that the price will be attractive or that we will be able to identify, acquire, finance or integrate such businesses successfully. In addition, in pursuing such acquisition opportunities, we may compete with other entities with similar growth strategies; these competitors may be larger and have greater financial and other resources than ARI. Competition for these acquisition targets could also result in increased prices of acquisition targets and/or a diminished pool of companies available for acquisition.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	The successful integration of these acquisitions also may involve a number of additional risks, including: (i) the inability to retain the clients of the acquired business; (ii) the lingering effects of poor client relations or service performance by the acquired business, which also may taint our existing business; (iii) the inability to retain the desirable management, key personnel and other employees of the acquired business; (iv) the inability to fully realize the desired efficiencies and economies of scale; (v) the inability to establish, implement or police ARI&#x2019;s existing standards, controls, procedures and policies in the acquired business; (vi) diversion of management attention; and (vii) exposure to client, employee and other legal claims for activities of the acquired business prior to acquisition. In addition, any acquired business could perform significantly worse than expected.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	The inability to identify, acquire, finance and successfully integrate acquisitions could have a material adverse effect on ARI or its estimated or desired business, income, growth or other condition and results.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Future acquisitions, financing arrangements or exercise of outstanding options and warrants may result in dilution to existing shareholders.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	The timing, size and success of acquisition efforts and any capital commitments cannot be readily predicted. Future acquisitions or investments may be financed by issuing shares of common stock, cash or a combination thereof. To the extent our common stock is used for all or a portion of the consideration to be paid for future acquisitions or investments, shareholders&#x2019; ownership will be diluted.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	We face risks with our international strategy.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Our business strategy includes increasing our presence in markets outside the U.S. This strategy presents a number of risks, including:
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	dealing with currency fluctuations;
</FONT>
</P>

</FONT>

	incorpor
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">

	6

	,

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	050
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	,000 as of July 31, 2016. We may not be able to maintain or increase profitability in the future. As a result of these historical losses, our financial position has been weakened, and our ability to finance our growth may be constrained.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">

</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Our unused net operating loss carryforwards could become impaired if we do not maintain profitability.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	We have federal net operating loss carryforwards (NOLs) of $
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	023
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	,000 as of July 31, 2016. We may not be able to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	generate
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	sufficient, timely taxable income to utilize these before they expire. As a result, both net income and income tax liabilities could be negatively impacted.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	We will require a significant amount of cash to service our indebtedness. Our ability to generate cash depends on certain factors beyond our control.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Our ability to make principal and interest payments on our indebtedness and to fund planned capital expenditures and product development efforts will depend on our ability to generate cash flow in the future. Our future operating performance and financial results will be subject, in part, to factors beyond our control, including dealer bankruptcies in the vertical markets we serve, and general economic, financial and business conditions. We cannot assure that our business will generate sufficient cash flow from operations or that future financing facilities will be available to us in an amount sufficient to enable us to pay our indebtedness or to fund our other liquidity needs.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
