<EFX_MANAGEMENTS_DISCUSSION>
<A NAME="FIS_MANAGEMENTS_DISCUSSION"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<A NAME="ARIS-20160731X10K_HTM_ITEM_7">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Item&nbsp;7
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Management&#x2019;s Discussion and Analysis of Financial Condition and Results of Operations
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	The following discussion of our results of operations and financial condition should be read together with our audited consolidated financial statements for
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	fiscal 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	fiscal 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	, including the notes thereto, which appear elsewhere in this Annual Report on Form 10-K. This discussion contains forward-looking statements, which as previously identified
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	are subject to the safe harbors created under the Securities Act and Exchange Act.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Overview
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	In f
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	iscal 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	ARI
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	achieve
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	d &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	record
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	results in revenue, operating inco
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	me, net income, Adjusted EBITDA and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	cash flow from operations.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Total revenue increased 17.9%, or $7,250,000, during fiscal 2016 over fiscal 2015. Recurring revenue increased 20.4% in fiscal 2016, compared to fiscal 2015, and constituted over 90% of our total revenue in both fiscal 2016 and 2015 as the Company continued to see growth in recurring revenue outpacing overall revenue growth. The growth in revenue is primarily attributable to revenue from the DCi, TASCO, and TCS acquisitions during fiscal 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	&nbsp;a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	nd
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	organic
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	revenue
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	growth
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Our operating income increased 53.2%, or $1,230,000, from $2,314,000 during fiscal 2015 to $3,544,000 during fiscal 2016. Operating expenses increased 14.6%, or $4,516,000, during fiscal 2016 compared to fiscal 2015, primarily due to the additional costs of our newly-acquired operations and additional expenses due to revenue growth
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	We continue to see the benefits of scale in our business as operating expenses as a percentage of sales decreased from 76.2% in fiscal 2015 to 74.1% in fiscal 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	The Company generated net income of $1,743,000 or $0.10 per share during fiscal 2016, compared to $1,071,000 or $0.07 per share during fiscal 2015. The increase in both operating and net
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	income
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	is primarily due to (i) operational efficiency improvements; (ii) organic revenue growth; and (iii) the growth in the overall business as a result of the acquisitions, while recognizing cost synergies from the combined businesses.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Cash flow from operations was $7,7
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	25
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	,000 during fiscal 2016, compared to $6,313,000 during fiscal 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
</P>
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;PUNCTUATION-WRAP:HANGING;VERTICAL-ALIGN:BASELINE;FONT-FAMILY:CG TIMES (W1);FONT-SIZE: 8PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
	17

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Total revenue increased 17.9% or $7,250,000 during fiscal 2016, compared to fiscal 2015. Recurring revenue increased 20.4% or $7,428,000 during fiscal 2016, compared to fiscal 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	, and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	represented 92.1% of total revenues during fiscal 2016 versus 90.2% during fiscal 2015. The increase in RR as a percentage of total revenue during fiscal 2016 was related to the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	decrease
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	revenue related to non-recurring professional services in the period as well as a continued focus of the Company to sell products that generate recurring revenue.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Lead Generation and eCommerce Website Revenue
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Our Lead Generation and eCommerce W
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	ebsite solutions generate revenue from one-time set-up and customization fees to develop new dealer websites, which is recognized ratably over the term of the contract, monthly recurring subscription fees and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	variable transaction fees. Our L
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	ead
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Generation and eCommerce W
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	ebsite solutions are typically sold as one year, renewable contracts with monthly payment terms. We currently host and maintain more
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	than 7,500 websites
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	for dealers in all
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	of our vertical markets. Lead Generation and eCommerce W
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	ebsite solutions have become ARI&#x2019;s largest source of revenue and accounted for 50.4% of total revenue during fiscal 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. Lead Generation and eCommerce W
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	ebsite revenue increased 8.0% to $24,028,000 in fiscal 2016, compared to $22,258,000 during fiscal 2015. This increase was a result of both organic re
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	venue growth from our historic Lead G
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	eneration and eCommerce solutions and revenue from the TCS eCommerce website solution that was acquired in Septembe
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	r 2014. We anticipate that our Lead Generation and eCommerce W
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	ebsite platforms will continue to be the Company&#x2019;s largest source of growth from a total revenue perspective, much of this growth coming in the ATW, AAPS and HME markets.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	eCatalog Revenue
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Our eCatalog solutions generate revenue from renewable subscription fees for our software, data content, software maintenance and support fees and software customization fees. eCatalog is our second largest source of RR, representing 37.5% of total revenue during fiscal 2016. eCatalo
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	g revenue increased 28.5% or $3,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	962,000 during fiscal 2016, compared to fiscal 2015 primarily as a result of our acquisition of DCi in July 2015. The catalog content provided in our eCatalog solutions help
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	s to drive sales growth in our Lead Generation and eCommerce W
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	ebsite solutions as well, so while eCatalog organic revenue growth is expected to be lower than our other products, it continues to drive growth in other areas of the business. Management expects eCatalog revenue
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	to increase at a low organic growth rate as the Company already has strong market share with this product.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Business Management Software Revenue
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Business management software revenue is generated from perpetual one-time license and installation fees for our new business management software, along with recurring maintenance and support fees, as well as hosting fees for our SaaS version
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Business management software revenue represented 6.4% of total revenue during fiscal 2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	16
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Business management software revenue increased 56.1% or $1,096,000 during fiscal 2016 as a result of both organic growth and revenue from TCS and TASCO
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	, which
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	were acquired in September 2014 and April 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	respectively. Management expects business management software revenue to increase in fiscal 2017 due to organic growth
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	, however, some of this growth depends upon non-recurring perpetual license sales which can be harder to project from a timing perspective.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Digital Marketing Solutions Revenue
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Revenues from our Digital Marketing S
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	olutions are generated from set-up fees and subscription fees for our lead generation tools through search engine optimization, social media marketing and website enhancements. We deri
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	ved 4.1% of our revenues from Digital Marketing S
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	ervices during fiscal 2016. Digital marketing revenue increased 57.5%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	from $1,228,000 during fiscal 2015 to $1,934,000 during fiscal 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	primarily due to organic growth from our existing offerings
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Management expects digital marketing revenue to increase as this service offering is a relatively new offering and is complementary to our other products, allowing us to expand within our current markets and current customers.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Other Revenue
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	We also offer a suite of complementary solutions, which include software, professional services and hosting services. Other revenue, which is primarily non-recurring in nature, represented approximately 1.7% of total revenue
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	, and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	decreased 38.7%, from $1,085,000 during fiscal 2015, to $801,000 during fiscal 2016. The decrease in other revenue is primarily due to a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	de
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	crease in our professional services revenue. Revenues from non-recurring professional services will fluctuate from period to period based on the timing of custom projects
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	and the Company has intentionally de-emphasized these projects as it focuses more on RR
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Recurring Revenue
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	RR is one of the most important growth drivers of our business. Increasing the percentage of our revenues that are recurring, while at the same time reducing the rate of customer churn, enhances our ability to generate profitable growth. Our subscription-based SaaS and DaaS products generate higher margins than our non-recurring products and services, and the incremental cost of selling these products to new dealers (we refer to these as new &#x201C;logos&#x201D;) is relatively low. Reducing the rate of our customer churn, which is the percentage of RR that does not renew, helps drive organic growth as it allows for a greater percentage of our new logos to be incremental to the top line (versus making up for lost logos) and also increases the base upon which we can apply price increases and sell additional products and features.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	We generate RR from each of our primary product categories from monthly license, subscription, maintenance and support fees. RR increased 20.4% from $36,483,000 during fiscal 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	to $43,911,000 during fiscal 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	primarily attributable to both the addition of RR from our acquisitions in fiscal 2016 and organic growth
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	We expect
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Lead Generation and eCommerce W
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	ebsite RR to continue to be our largest contributor to RR growth in fiscal 2017.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Non-recurring Revenue
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Non-recurring revenue is generated from one-time perpetual license fees from our business management offerings, certain offerings within the Company&#x2019;s digital marketing services, professional services related to software customization and data conversion, usage fees charged on our RR products, set-up fees and other complementary products and services. Total non-recurring revenue decreased 4.5% from $3,960,000 during fiscal 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	to $3,782,000 during fiscal 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	primarily due
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	decreased professional services revenue partially offset by increased perpetual license revenue from software management solutions. Our goal is to maintain non-recurring revenue of less than 10% of total revenue, as the margins on this revenue tends to be lower than our RR products. Furthermore, non-recurring revenue must be resold each year.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Gross profit was $38
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	,887,000 or 81.5% of revenue in fiscal 2016, compared to $33,141,000 or 81.9% of revenue for fiscal 2015. The decrease in gross profit margin was due to investments made to migrate website customers from older platforms that we are no longer actively selling
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	to newer platforms,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	and an increase i
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	n
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	royalty costs as we continue to expand our product offerings
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
</P>
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;PUNCTUATION-WRAP:HANGING;VERTICAL-ALIGN:BASELINE;FONT-FAMILY:CG TIMES (W1);FONT-SIZE: 8PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
	19
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<HR SIZE="3" STYLE="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<P STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage20"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Amortization of capitalized software costs as a percentage of revenue decreased during fiscal 2016, compared to last year, primarily due to revenue increasing at a faster rate than software capitalization costs in recent years. Direct labor costs as a percentage of revenue increased during fiscal 2016, compared to last year
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	primarily due to: (i) an increase in our digital marketing revenue, which has higher direct costs than our other products; (ii) an increase in website implementations; and (iii) the migration of customer websites in an effort to consolidate our customers to the product most suited to their industry and consolidate our website platforms
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Other direct costs increased as a percentage of revenue during fiscal 2016, compared to fiscal 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	due to increased third party costs associated with our digital marketing and website add-on offerings and fees paid to outside contractors for assistance with the website
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	migrations and custom professional service projects.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	The Company expects fluctuations in gross margin from quarter
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	quarter and year
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	over
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	year based on sales bookings, the mix of products sold, and the nature of any ongoing website platform migrations.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Operating Expenses

	We categorize net operating expenses as follows:

<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:8PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	Exclusive of amortization of software product costs of $2,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:8PT;COLOR:#000000;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:8PT;COLOR:#000000;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:8PT;COLOR:#000000;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:8PT;COLOR:#000000;">
	and 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:8PT;COLOR:#000000;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	Net operating expenses increased 14.6% or $4,516,000 during fiscal 2016, compared to fiscal 2015. The Company acquired the net assets of TCS in September 2014, the net assets of TASCO in April 2015 and the net assets of DCi in July 2015. The increase in net operating expenses was primarily due to the costs nece
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	ssary to operate the acquired businesse
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	s for
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	full 12 months
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	in fiscal 2016,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	as compared to the TCS office for
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	only
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	10 months, the TASCO office for 3 months and the DCi office for part of July
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	in fiscal
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	Net operating expenses as a percentage of sales decreased from 76.2% in fiscal 2015 to 74.1% in fiscal 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	This is primarily a result of operational efficiencies and revenue growth
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	To the extent the Company can leverage growth in its core RR products, management expects net operating expenses to decline as a percentage of total revenues, as incremental costs related to these products decrease for every dollar of new revenue.
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage21"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Sales and Marketing
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Sales and marketing expense increased 4.0% or $420,000 during fiscal 2016, compared to fiscal 2015. The increase was primarily a result of the cost of the sales staff associated with the DCi operation. Sales and marketing expense as a percentage of revenue decreased from 25.8% of revenue in fiscal 2015 to 22.7% for the same period in fiscal 2016. This decrease is due to the growth in our RR base, which requires much less resources to renew. Management expects sales and marketing expense as a percentage of revenue to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	be flat or down
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	as RR continues to grow.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Customer Operations and Support
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Customer operations and support expense increased 27.3% or $2,129,000 during fiscal 2016, compared to fiscal 2015, and as a percentage of revenue increased from 19.3% of revenue during fiscal 2015 to 20.8% during fiscal 2016. The customer operations and support functions of an acquired business typically take longer to fully integrate due to merging software platforms, help desks and customer hosting systems in order to operate more efficiently. Management expects customer operations and support expenses to decline as a percentage of revenue over time,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	to the extent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	we continue to integrate these areas into our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	operations and we supplement labor capacity in our India office,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	while RR continues to grow.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Software Development and Technical Support
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Our software development and technical support staff have three essential responsibilities for which the accounting treatment varies depending upon the work performed: (i) costs associated with internal software development efforts (after technological feasibility is established) are capitalized as software product costs and amortized over the estimated useful lives of the product; (ii) costs for professional services performed for customers related to software customization projects are classified as cost of revenue; and (iii) all other activities, including research and development, are considered operating expenses and included within the software development and technical support operating expense category.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Software development and technical support costs increased 21.3% or $894,000 during fiscal 2016 versus fiscal 2015, primarily due to the additional development staff associated with the TCS products and additional capacity related to the Company&#x2019;s continued focus to reduce churn. During fiscal 2016, we capitalized $1,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	302
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	,000 of software development labor
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	overhead
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	and interest expense
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	, versus $1,0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	91
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	,000 during fiscal 2015. In addition to internal capitalized software costs, we had outsourced development
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	costs of $
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	478
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	during fiscal 2016 and $320,000 during fiscal 2015.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	W
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	e devoted
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	much of these
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	resources to a major upgrade of our website products
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	during
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	fiscal 2016.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	We expect fluctuations in the percentage of software development and technical support costs classified as operating expenses from period-to-period, based on the mix of research and prototype work versus capitalized software development and professional services activities
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	General and Administrative
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	General and administrative expense increased 6.4% or $422,000 during fiscal 2016, compared to fiscal 2015. The increase was primarily a result of additional headcount from the TCS and DCi acquisitions. General and administrative expense as a percentage of revenue decreased from 16.4% of revenue for fiscal 2015 to 14.8% for the same period in fiscal 2016. Management expects general and administrative expense as a percentage of revenue to decrease over time as we continue to scale the business, although additional acquisitions or other transactions could result in elevated general and administrative expense in future periods.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>

</EFX_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Interest expense is composed of both interest paid on the Company&#x2019;s debt financing arrangements and amortization of non-cash interest charges related to deferred finance costs and imputed interest on contingent liabilities
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Interest expense remained relatively unchanged in fiscal 2016 as compared to 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	This is a result of the Company continuing to pay down outstanding debt balances partially offset by an increase in the Prime Rate of interest.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	The Company expects interest expense to decrease
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	in fiscal 2017
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	, compared to fiscal 2016, due to the continued pay down of outstanding debt.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
</P>
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;PUNCTUATION-WRAP:HANGING;VERTICAL-ALIGN:BASELINE;FONT-FAMILY:CG TIMES (W1);FONT-SIZE: 8PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
	21
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<HR SIZE="3" STYLE="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<P STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage22"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Adjusted EBITDA
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	EBITDA is calculated as net income adjusted to exclude interest expense, amortization, depreciation and income tax expense. Adjusted EBITDA further eliminates non-cash, stock-based compensation expense
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Management believes Adjusted EBITDA is helpful in understanding period-over-period operating results separate and apart from non-operating expenses and expenses pertaining to prior period investing activities, particularly given the Company&#x2019;s significant investments in capitalized software and its continuing efforts in completing acquisitions, which typically result in significant non-cash depreciation and amortization expense in subsequent periods
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	However, Adjusted EBITDA has significant limitations as an analytical tool and should only be used cautiously in addition to, and never as a substitute for, operating income, cash flows or other measures of financial performance prepared in accordance with generally accepted accounting principles and may not necessarily be comparable to similarly titled measures of other companies.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	The table below presents the reconciliation of net income to EBITDA and Adjusted EBITDA for
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	fiscal 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	fiscal
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	(in thousands):
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Adjusted EBITDA increased 29.3%, from $6,572,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	000 during fiscal 2015 to $8,496
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	,000 during fiscal 2016. Adjusted EBITDA as a percentage of revenue increased from 16.3% during fiscal 2015 to 17.8% during fiscal 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	The increase was primarily due to the improvement in operating income and an increase in depreciation and amortization expense. Management expects Adjusted EBITDA to increase in fiscal 2016, to the extent earnings continue to increase as a result of RR growth.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">

	payment equal to $3,750,000; (ii
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	) 159,795 shares of th
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	e Company&#x2019;s common stock; and (iii
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	) the issuance of a promissory note in principal amount of $2,000,000 to DCi. The principal amount of the DCi
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	n
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	ote was reduced by approximately $64,000 as a result of post-closing adjustments to the estimated valuation of the net assets acquired, pursuant to the terms of the asset purchase agreement
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. &nbsp;

	On April 27, 2015, the Company acquired substantially all of the assets of TASCO Corporation&nbsp;and its affiliated company Signal Extraprise Corporation (collectively &#x201C;TASCO&#x201D;), a leading provider of business management software designed exclusively for&nbsp;the automotive tire and wheel aftermarket industry.&nbsp;Consideration

	&#x2019;s revolving credit facility; (ii
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	) 242,424 shares of th
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	e Company&#x2019;s common stock; and (iii
</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	The Company&#x2019;s strategy is to integrate the sales teams from acquisitions as quickly as possible in order to realize cross selling synergies. As a result, we do not track revenues and costs specific to the individual acquired businesses.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Income Taxes
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	The Company has net deferred tax assets of $
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	9
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	,000 as of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	July 31, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	, &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	primarily consisting of net operating loss
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	carryforwards (&#x201C;NOLs&#x201D;) and book-to-
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	tax temporary differences. Income tax expense is provided for at the applicable statutory tax rate applied to current U.S. income before taxes, plus or minus any adjustments to the deferred tax assets and to the estimated valuation allowance against deferred tax assets. Income tax expense does not represent a significant current cash obligation, as we continue to have NOLs to offset substantially all of the taxable income.
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	We generated $2,834,000 of net cash during fiscal 2016, compared to the $476,000 during fiscal 2015. We generated net cash
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	from
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	operating activities of $7,7
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	25
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	,000 during fiscal 2016 compared to $6,313,000 during fiscal 2015. This increase in cash generated from operations was primarily due to increased pre-tax profitability, and higher non-cash depreciation and amortization expense as a result of our acquisitions in fiscal 2015.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Cash used in investing
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	activities
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	decreased $8,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	446
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	,000 during fiscal 2016, compared to fiscal 2015. During fiscal 2015, we paid cash of $4,200,000 as consideration for the TCS acquisition, $1,750,000 as consideration for the TASCO acquisition and $3,750,000 as consideration for the DCi acquisition
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	, while we had no acquisitions in fiscal 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. These decreases were partially offset by increased investment in equipment and software development costs as we upgraded the equipment in our data centers
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	, built out our India office, invested in an enterprise CRM system
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	and invested more heavily in product improvements
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	We will continue to invest cash in the business to further our growth strategies previously discussed.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Net cash used in financing activities was $1,3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	81
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	,000 during fiscal 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	, as the Company made payments
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	o
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	n
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	its outstanding debt. Net cash provided by financing activities was
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	$
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	6,127,000 in fiscal 2015 as the Company increased its senior debt, as described below, to partially fund the TCS acquisition in September 2014, and generated $4,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	756
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	,000 from the sale of the Company&#x2019;s common stock pursuant to an underwritten offering
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	On May 12, 2015, the Company completed an underwritten offering pursuant to which it sold 1,760,000 shares of its common stock at a price to the public of $3.00 per share. The Company received net proceeds of approximately $4,686,300 from the sale, after deducting underwriting discounts and commissions and estimated offering expenses payable by the Company. The Company used a portion of the net proceeds to fund the DCi acquisition and a portion to repay its outstanding line of credit balance of $1,750,000 incurred in connection with its April 2015 acquisition of TASCO (thus making the line of credit fully available for future transactions).
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	The Company borrowed an additional $2.1 million on the Silicon Valley Bank (&#x201C;SVB&#x201D;) term note and $1.5 million on the SVB revolving credit line (each as described below) to partially fund its acquisition of TCS on September 30, 2014. The balance on the revolving credit line was subsequently repaid by the Company. The Company also issued two promissory notes in the aggregate principal amount of $3,000,000 in connection with the TCS acquisition and one promissory note in the principal amount of $2,000,000 in connection with the DCi acquisition.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Critical Accounting Policies
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	The Company&#x2019;s discussion and analysis of its financial condition and results of operations are based upon its financial statements, which have been prepared in accordance with accounting principles generally accepted in the United States (&#x201C;GAAP&#x201D;). The preparation of financial statements in conformance with GAAP requires estimates and assumptions that affect the reported amounts of assets, liabilities, revenues and expenses and related disclosure of contingent assets and liabilities. The SEC has defined a company&#x2019;s critical accounting policies as the ones that are most important to the portrayal of a company&#x2019;s financial condition and results of operations, and which require us to make our most difficult and subjective judgments, often as a result of the need to make estimates of matters that are inherently uncertain. Based on this definition, we have identified as the most critical accounting policies and judgments those addressed below. We also have other key accounting policies, which involve the use of estimates, judgments and assumptions that are significant to understanding our results. For additional information, refer to Note 1 of the consolidated financial statements, which appear elsewhere within this report on Form 10-K. Although we believe that our estimates, assumptions, and judgments are reasonable, they are based upon information currently available. Actual results may differ significantly from these estimates under different assumptions, judgments or conditions.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
</P>
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;PUNCTUATION-WRAP:HANGING;VERTICAL-ALIGN:BASELINE;FONT-FAMILY:CG TIMES (W1);FONT-SIZE: 8PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
	24
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<HR SIZE="3" STYLE="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<P STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage25"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Revenue Recognition
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:5PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	Revenues from subscription fees for use of our software, access to our catalog content and software maintenance and support fees are all recognized ratably over the contractual term of the arrangement. The Company accounts for delivered elements in accordance with the selling price when arrangements include multiple product components or other elements and vendor-specific objective evidence exists for the value of all undelivered elements. Revenue on undelivered elements is recognized when the elements are delivered. ARI considers all arrangements with payment terms extending beyond 12 months not to be fixed or determinable and evaluates other arrangements with payment terms longer than normal to determine whether the arrangement is fixed or determinable. If the fee is not fixed or determinable, revenue is recognized as payments become due from the customer. Arrangements that include acceptance terms beyond the standard terms are not recognized until acceptance has occurred. If collectability is not considered probable, revenue is recognized when the fee is collected.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:5PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	For software license arrangements that do not require significant modification or customization of the underlying software, the Company recognizes revenue when persuasive evidence of an arrangement exists, delivery has occurred, the fee is fixed or determinable and collectability is probable.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	Revenues for professional services to customize complex features and functionality in a product&#x2019;s base software code or develop complex interfaces within a customer&#x2019;s environment are recognized as the services are performed if they are determined to have stand-alone value to the customer or if all of following conditions are met
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;(
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	i) the customer has a contractual right to take possession of the software;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	(
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	ii) the customer will not incur significant penalty if it exercises this right; and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	(
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	iii) it is feasible for the customer to either run the software on its own hardware or contract with another unrelated party to host the software. When the current estimates of total contract revenue for professional services and the total related costs indicate a loss, a provision for the entire loss on the contract is made in the period the amount is determined
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	Professional service revenues for set-up and integration of hosted websites, or other services considered essential to the functionality of other elements of the arrangement, are
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	recogn
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	ized over the term of the contract.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Trade Receivables, Credit Policy and Allowance for Doubtful Accounts
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Trade receivables are uncollateralized customer obligations due on normal trade terms, most of which require payment within thirty (30) days from the invoice date. Payments of trade receivables are allocated to the specific invoices identified on the customer&#x2019;s remittance advice or, if unspecified, are applied to the earliest unpaid invoices.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	The carrying amount of trade receivables is reduced by an allowance that reflects management&#x2019;s best estimate of the amounts that will not be collected. Management individually reviews receivable balances based on an assessment of current creditworthiness and estimates the portion of the balance that will not be collected. The allowance for potential doubtful accounts is reflected as an offset to trade receivables in the accompanying balance sheets.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Deferred Income Taxes
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	The tax effect of the temporary differences between the book and tax basis of assets and liabilities and the estimated tax benefit from tax net operating losses is reported as deferred tax assets and liabilities in the consolidated balance sheet. An assessment of the likelihood that net deferred tax assets will be realized from future taxable income is performed periodically. Because the ultimate realizability of deferred tax assets is highly subject to the outcome of future events, the amount established as a valuation allowance is considered to be a significant estimate that is subject to change in the near term. To the extent a valuation allowance is established or there is a change in the allowance during a period, the change is reflected with a corresponding increase or decrease in the tax provision in the statement of income. Future events that could have a material impact on the valuation allowance include, but are not limited to, acquisitions, triggering a limitation of use under Section 382 of the Internal Revenue Code and changes in tax legislation.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Stock-Based Compensation
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	We use the Black-Scholes model to value stock options granted.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Expected volatility is based on historical volatility of the Company&#x2019;s stock. The expected life of options granted represents the period of time that options granted are expected to be outstanding. The risk-free rate for periods within the contractual term of the options is based on the U.S. Treasury yields in effect at the time of grant. As stock-based compensation expense recognized in our results of operations is based on awards ultimately expected to vest, the amount has been reduced for estimated forfeitures, which were estimated based on our historical experience.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Management reviews the critical assumptions used in the Black-Scholes model each quarter and adjusts those assumptions when necessary.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
</P>
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;PUNCTUATION-WRAP:HANGING;VERTICAL-ALIGN:BASELINE;FONT-FAMILY:CG TIMES (W1);FONT-SIZE: 8PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
	25
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">

	&nbsp;

<A NAME="eolPage26"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Goodwill and Other Intangible Assets
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	As fully described in Note 1 to the consolidated financial statements, we annually review the carrying value of goodwill to determine whether an impairment may exist. We determined that there is a single reporting unit for the purpose of goodwill impairment testing. We estimate the fair value of the reporting unit using various valuation techniques, with our primary techniques being a discounted cash flow valuation and control premium adjusted market capitalization. There are many estimates and assumptions involved in preparing a discounted cash flow analysis, including estimating future operating results, selecting a weighted average cost of capital to discount estimated future cash flows, anticipated long-term growth rates and future profit margins.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Estimating the fair value of a reporting unit is an inherently subjective process. Changes in assumptions, estimates, and other inputs could result in the indication of potential impairment of a portion of the recorded goodwill. Management believes the assumptions, estimates and other inputs used reflect our best efforts and are appropriate for valuing the reporting unit. Our goodwill impairment test indicated that goodwill was not impaired in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	fiscal 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	fiscal 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Impairment tests are also performed for those intangible assets with estimable useful lives if circumstances indicate that an impairment event may have occurred
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Quarterly Financial Data
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	The following table sets forth the unaudited results of operations for each of the eight quarterly periods ended
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	July 31, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	, prepared on a basis consistent with the audited financial statements, reflecting all normal recurring adjustments that are considered necessary. The quarterly information is as follows (in thousands, except per share data):
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

	. &nbsp;

	Quantitative and Qualitative Disclosures About Market Risk

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

	We are a smaller reporting company as defined by Rule 12b-2 of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934

</FONT>

	, and are not required to provide the information under this item.

<EFX_CONTROL_AND_PROCEDURES>
<A NAME="FIS_CONTROL_AND_PROCEDURES"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<A NAME="ARIS-20160731X10K_HTM_ITEM_9A">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Item 9A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Controls and Procedures
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Evaluation of Disclosure Controls and Procedures
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	We maintain disclosure controls and procedures designed to ensure that information required to be disclosed in our reports filed under the Exchange Act, as amended, is recorded, processed, summarized and reported within the required time periods and that such information is accumulated and communicated to our management, including our Chief Executive Officer and Chief Financial Officer, as appropriate, to allow for timely decisions regarding required disclosure.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
</P>
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;PUNCTUATION-WRAP:HANGING;VERTICAL-ALIGN:BASELINE;FONT-FAMILY:CG TIMES (W1);FONT-SIZE: 8PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
	26
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<HR SIZE="3" STYLE="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<P STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage27"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	As required by Rule 13a-15 under the Exchange Act, we have completed an evaluation, under the supervision and with the participation of our management, including the Chief Executive Officer and the Chief Financial Officer, of the effectiveness and the design and operation of our disclosure controls and procedures as of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	July 31, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. Based upon this evaluation, our management, including the Chief Executive Officer and the Chief Financial Officer, has concluded that our disclosure controls and procedures were effective as of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	July 31, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Management&#x2019;s Annual Report on Internal Control over Financial Reporting
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Our management is responsible for establishing and maintaining adequate internal control over financial reporting as defined in Rules 13a-15(f) and 15d-15(f) under the Exchange Act. Under the supervision and with the participation of our management, including our Chief Executive Officer and the Chief Financial Officer, we conducted an evaluation of the effectiveness of our internal control over financial reporting based on the framework in Internal Control over Financial Reporting &#x2013; Guidance for Smaller Public Companies issued by the Committee of Sponsoring Organizations of the Treadway Commission. Based on our evaluation under this framework, our management concluded that our internal control over financial reporting was effective as of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	July 31, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	This Annual Report on Form 10-K does not include an attestation report of our independent registered public accounting firm regarding internal control over financial reporting. Internal control over financial reporting was not subject to attestation by our independent registered public accounting firm based on our status as a non-accelerated filer
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	We are required to provide only management&#x2019;s report in this Annual Report on Form 10-K.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Changes in Internal Controls
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	There were no changes to the Company&#x2019;s internal control over financial reporting during the year ended
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	July 31, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	that have materially affected, or are reasonably likely to materially affect, the Company&#x2019;s internal control over financial reporting.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Limitations on Effectiveness of Controls and Procedures
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Our management, including our Chief Executive Officer and Chief Financial Officer, does not expect that our disclosure controls and procedures or our internal controls will prevent all errors and all fraud. A control system, no matter how well conceived and operated, can provide only reasonable, not absolute, assurance that the objectives of the control system are met. Further, the design of a control system must reflect the fact that there are resource constraints and the benefits of controls must be considered relative to their costs. Because of the inherent limitations in all control systems, no evaluation of controls can provide absolute assurance that all control issues and instances of fraud, if any, within the Company have been detected. These inherent limitations include, but are not limited to, the realities that judgments in decision-making can be faulty and that breakdowns can occur because of simple error or mistake. Additionally, controls can be circumvented by the individual acts of some persons, by collusion of two or more people or by management override of the control. The design of any system of controls also is based in part upon certain assumptions about the likelihood of future events and there can be no assurance that any design will succeed in achieving its stated goals under all potential future conditions. Over time, controls may become inadequate because of changes in conditions, or the degree of compliance with the policies or procedures may deteriorate. Because of the inherent limitations in a cost-effective control system, misstatements due to error or fraud may occur and not be detected.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
</EFX_CONTROL_AND_PROCEDURES>
