<EFX_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="WIDTH:05.26%;BORDER-TOP:1PT SOLID #000000 ;BORDER-LEFT:1PT SOLID #000000 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT SOLID #000000 ;BORDER-RIGHT:1PT SOLID #000000 ;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #CCEEFF;HEIGHT:25.50PT;PADDING:0PT;">
<A NAME="FIS_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE_16"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 8PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
	2.1
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="WIDTH:94.74%;BORDER-TOP:1PT SOLID #000000 ;BORDER-LEFT:1PT SOLID #000000 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT SOLID #000000 ;BORDER-RIGHT:1PT SOLID #000000 ;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #CCEEFF;HEIGHT:25.50PT;PADDING:0PT;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	of Indep

</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	endent Registered Public Accounting Firm
</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	To the Board of Directors and Shareholders&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	ARI Network Services, Inc.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	We have audited the accompanying consolidated balance sheets of ARI Network Services, Inc. and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	its
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Subsidiar
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	ies
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	&nbsp;(
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	&#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	the Company
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	&#x201D;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	) as of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	July 31, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	and 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	, and the related consolidated statements of operations, comprehensive income (loss), shareholders&#x2019; equity and cash flows for each of the years in the two-year period ended
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	July 31, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. The Company&#x2019;s management is responsible for these financial statements. Our responsibility is to express an opinion on these financial statements based on our audits.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	We conducted our audits in accordance with standards of the Public Company Accounting Oversight Board (United States). Those standards require that we plan and perform the audits to obtain reasonable assurance about whether the consolidated financial statements are free of material misstatement. The Company is not required to have, nor were we engaged to perform, an audit of its internal control over financial reporting. Our audits included consideration of internal control over financial reporting as a basis for designing audit procedures that are appropriate in the circumstances, but not for the purpose of expressing an opinion on the effectiveness of the Company&#x2019;s internal control over financial reporting. Accordingly, we express no such opinion. An audit also includes examining, on a test basis, evidence supporting the amounts and disclosures in the consolidated financial statements, assessing the accounting principles used and significant estimates made by management, as well as evaluating the overall financial statement presentation. We believe that our audits provide a reasonable basis for our opinion.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	In our opinion, the consolidated financial statements referred to above present fairly, in all material respects, the financial position of the Company as of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	July 31, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	and 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	, and the results of its operations and its cash flows for each of the years in the two-year period ended
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	July 31, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	, in conformity with accounting principles generally accepted in the United States
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT -36PT 0PT -18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT -36PT 0PT -18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	ARI Network Services, Inc.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<EFX_NOTES_TO_FINANCIAL_STATEMENT>
<A NAME="FIS_NOTES_TO_FINANCIAL_STATEMENT"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT -36PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Notes to Consolidated Financial Statements
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:5PT 3.6PT 5PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Description of the Business and Significant Accounting Policies&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:5PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Description of the Business &nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:5PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	ARI Network Services, Inc. (&#x201C;ARI&#x201D; or &#x201C;the Company&#x201D;) creates software-as-a-service (&#x201C;SaaS&#x201D;), data-as-a-service (&#x201C;DaaS&#x201D;) and other solutions that help equipment manufacturers, distributors and dealers in selected vertical markets to Sell More Stuff!&#x2122; &#x2013; online and in-store.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	We&nbsp;remove the complexity of selling and servicing new and used whole goods inventory and PG&amp;A for customers in the automotive tire and wheel aftermarket (&#x201C;ATW&#x201D;), automotive aftermarket parts and service (&#x201C;AAPS&#x201D;), powersports, outdoor power equipment (&#x201C;OPE&#x201D;), marine, home medical equipment (&#x201C;HME&#x201D;), recreational vehicles (&#x201C;RV&#x201D;) and appliance industries.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	Our innovative products are powered by a proprietary library of enriched original equipment and aftermarket content from over
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	1,800
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	manufacturers. More than
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	23,500
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	equipment dealers, distributors and manufacturers worldwide leverage our web and eCatalog platforms to Sell More Stuff!
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	&#x2122;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	We were incorporated in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Wisconsin
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	in 1981. Our principal executive office and headquarters is located in Milwaukee, Wisconsin. The office address is 10850 West Park Place, Suite 1200, Milwaukee, WI 53224, and our telephone number at that location is (414) 973-4300. Our principal website address is
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	www.arinet.com
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. ARI also maintains operations in Cypress, California; Floyds Knobs, Indiana; Des Moines, Iowa; Duluth, Minnesota; Wexford, Pennsylvania; Cookeville, Tennessee;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	Salt Lake City, Utah;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Leiden, The Netherlands; and Gurgaon, India.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:5PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Basis of Presentation
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:5PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	These consolidated financial statements include the consolidated financial statements of ARI and its wholly-owned subsidiaries, ARI Europe B.V. and ARI Network Services Pvt. Ltd. and have been prepared in accordance with accounting principles generally accepted in the United States (&#x201C;GAAP&#x201D;). We eliminated all significant intercompany balances and transactions in consolidation. All adjustments that, in the opinion of management, are necessary for a fair presentation of the periods presented have been reflected as required by Regulation S-X, Rule 10-01.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:5PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Fiscal Year&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:5PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Our fiscal year ends on July 31. References to fiscal 2016, for example, refer to the fiscal year ended July 31, 2016, and references to fiscal 2015 refer to the fiscal year ended July 31, 2015.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:5PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Foreign Currency Translation&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:5PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	The functional currency of the Company&#x2019;s subsidiary in the Netherlands is the Euro and in India it is the Rupee. Accordingly, monetary assets and liabilities are translated into U.S. dollars at the rate of exchange existing at the end of the period, and non-monetary assets and liabilities are translated into U.S. dollars at historical exchange rates. Translation gains and losses are translated at the weighted-average exchange rates during the period and expensed to other income (expense)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Adjustments resulting from the re-measurement of the consolidated financial statements into the reporting currency are charged or credited to comprehensive income (loss)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:5PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Use of Estimates&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:5PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	The preparation of the Company&#x2019;s consolidated financial statements in conformity with GAAP requires management to make estimates and assumptions that affect the amounts reported in the consolidated financial statements and accompanying notes. Actual results could differ from those estimates. The Company considers capitalization and amortization of software product costs, valuation and useful life of intangible assets, goodwill, allowance for bad debt, contingent liabilities for anticipated future earn-out payments, valuation of stock-based compensation and the deferred tax valuation allowance to be significant estimates subject to change in the near term
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
</P>
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;PUNCTUATION-WRAP:HANGING;VERTICAL-ALIGN:BASELINE;FONT-FAMILY:CG TIMES (W1);FONT-SIZE: 8PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
	36
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<HR SIZE="3" STYLE="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<P STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage37"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;BACKGROUND-COLOR:LIME;">
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:5PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Revenue Recognition
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:5PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	Revenues from subscription fees for use of our software, access to our catalog content, and software maintenance and support fees are all recognized ratably over the contractual term of the arrangement. The Company has customer contracts with multiple services or elements, which may be delivered at different times. The Company accounts for delivered elements in accordance with the selling price when arrangements include multiple product components or other elements and vendor-specific objective evidence exists for the value of all undelivered elements. Revenue on undelivered elements is recognized when the elements are delivered. ARI considers all arrangements with payment terms extending beyond 12 months not to be fixed or determinable and evaluates other arrangements with payment terms longer than normal to determine whether the arrangement is fixed or determinable. If the fee is not fixed or determinable, revenue is recognized as payments become due from the customer. Arrangements that include acceptance terms beyond the standard terms are not recognized until acceptance has occurred. If collectability is not considered probable, revenue is recognized when the fee is collected.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:5PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	For software license arrangements that do not require significant modification or customization of the underlying software, the Company recognizes revenue when persuasive evidence of an arrangement exists, delivery has occurred, the fee is fixed or determinable and collectability is probable.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:5PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	Revenues for professional services to customize complex features and functionality in a product&#x2019;s base software code or develop complex interfaces within a customer&#x2019;s environment are recognized as the services are performed if they are determined to have standalone value to the customer or if all of the following conditions are met
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	(
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	i) the customer has a contractual right to take possession of the software;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	(
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	ii) the customer will not incur significant penalty if it exercises this right; and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	(
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	iii) it is feasible for the customer to either run the software on its own hardware or contract with another unrelated party to host the software. When the current estimates of total contract revenue for professional services and the total related costs indicate a loss, a provision for the entire loss on the contract is made in the period the amount is determined. Professional service revenues for set-up and integration of hosted websites, or other services considered essential to the functionality of other elements of the arrangement, are amortized over the term of the contract.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:5PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	Revenue for variable transaction fees, primarily for use of the shopping cart feature of our websites, is recognized as it is earned.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:5PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	Amounts received for shipping and handling fees are reflected in revenue. Costs incurred for shipping and handling are reported in cost of revenue.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:5PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	Amounts invoiced to customers prior to recognition as revenue, as discussed above, are reflected in the accompanying balance sheets as deferred revenue.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	No
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	single customer accounted for
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	10%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	or more of ARI&#x2019;s revenue during fiscal 2016 or 2015.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Cash and Cash Equivalents&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:5PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	We consider all highly liquid debt instruments purchased with an original maturity of three months or less to be cash equivalents
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:5PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Trade Receivables, Credit Policy and Allowance for Doubtful Accounts
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:5PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Trade receivables are uncollateralized customer obligations due on normal trade terms, most of which require payment within thirty (30) days from the invoice date. Payments of trade receivables are allocated to the specific invoices identified on the customer&#x2019;s remittance advice or, if unspecified, are applied to the earliest unpaid invoices.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:5PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	The carrying amount of trade receivables is reduced by an allowance that reflects management&#x2019;s best estimate of the amounts that will not be collected. Management individually reviews receivable balances that exceed ninety (
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	90
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	) days from the invoice date and, based on an assessment of current creditworthiness, estimates the portion of the balance that will not be collected. The allowance for potential doubtful accounts is reflected as an offset to trade receivables in the accompanying consolidated balance sheets.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:5PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Work in Process&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:5PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Work in process consists of services provided by the Company, for which revenue was recognized and billing is done in arrears and has not been invoiced as of the end of the reporting period
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:5PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
</P>
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;PUNCTUATION-WRAP:HANGING;VERTICAL-ALIGN:BASELINE;FONT-FAMILY:CG TIMES (W1);FONT-SIZE: 8PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
	37
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
</FONT>
</P>

	Equipment and leasehold improvements are stated at cost. 	. &nbsp;

</EFX_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:5PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Capitalized and Purchased Software Product Costs
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:5PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Certain software development and acquisition costs are capitalized when incurred. Capitalization of these costs begins upon the establishment of technological feasibility. The establishment of technological feasibility and the on-going assessment of recoverability of software costs require considerable judgment by management with respect to certain external factors, including, but not limited to, the determination of technological feasibility, anticipated future gross revenue, estimated economic life and changes in software and hardware technologies.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	The Company capitalizes software enhancements on an on-going basis and all other software development and support expenditures are charged to expense in the period incurred.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:5PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	The annual amortization of software products is computed using the straight-line method over the estimated economic life of the product, which currently ranges from
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	14
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	years. Amortization starts when the product is available for general release to customers.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:5PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Deferred Loan Fees and Debt Discounts
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:5PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	Fees associated with securing debt are capitalized and shown as contra-debt, reducing the carrying amount of long-term debt on the consolidated balance sheet. Deferred loan fees and debt discounts are amortized to interest expense over the life of the debt using the effective interest method.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:5PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Impairment of Long-Lived Assets&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:5PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	In accordance with GAAP, long-lived assets, including capitalized software product costs, property and equipment and amortized intangible assets, are reviewed for impairment whenever events or changes in circumstances indicate that the carrying amount may not be recoverable. If the sum of the expected undiscounted cash flows is less than the carrying value of the related asset or group of assets, a loss is recognized for the difference between the fair value and carrying value of the asset or group of assets. Such analyses necessarily involve judgment.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:5PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Goodwill &nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:5PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	GAAP requires that we assess goodwill for impairment annually, or more frequently if circumstances indicate that an impairment event may have occurred. Certain triggering events that may warrant a more frequent impairment test include a significant change in the business climate, legal factors, a decline in operating performance, competition, sale or disposition of a significant portion of the business, or other factors
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Our annual assessment date is July 31.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:5PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	We test goodwill for impairment using a two-step process, as prescribed by GAAP.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	The first step of the test is used to identify potential impairment by comparing the fair value of a reporting unit with its carrying amount, including goodwill. If the carrying amount of a reporting unit exceeds its fair value, the second step of the goodwill impairment test is performed to measure the amount of impairment loss, if any. The second step of the goodwill impairment test compares the implied fair value of the reporting unit&#x2019;s goodwill with the carrying amount of that goodwill. If the carrying amount of the reporting unit&#x2019;s goodwill exceeds the implied fair value of that goodwill, an impairment loss is recognized in an amount equal to that excess.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	We determined there is a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	single
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	reporting unit for the purpose of goodwill impairment tests.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	We estimate the fair value of the reporting unit using various valuation techniques, with the primary techniques being a market capitalization test and a discounted cash flow analysis. There are many estimates and assumptions involved in preparing a discounted cash flow analysis, including most significantly the weighted average cost of capital (&#x201C;WACC&#x201D;) used to discount future cash flows, anticipated long-term growth rates and future profit margins. Management uses its best efforts to reasonably estimate all of these and other inputs in the cash flow models utilized. We estimated future cash flows using multiple forecast scenarios and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	management used its judgment to assign a weighting
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	to each scenario.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:5PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
</P>
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;PUNCTUATION-WRAP:HANGING;VERTICAL-ALIGN:BASELINE;FONT-FAMILY:CG TIMES (W1);FONT-SIZE: 8PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
	38
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<HR SIZE="3" STYLE="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<P STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage39"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:5PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	Step 1 of the goodwill impairment test indicated that goodwill was
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	not
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	impaired in fiscal 2016 or fiscal 2015. As a result, step 2 of the test was not performed.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:5PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Deferred Income Taxes&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	The tax effect of the temporary differences between the book and tax bases of assets and liabilities and the estimated tax benefit from tax net operating losses is reported as deferred tax assets and liabilities in the consolidated balance sheets. An assessment of the likelihood that net deferred tax assets will be realized from future taxable income is performed at each reporting date or when events or changes in circumstances indicate that there may be a change in the valuation allowance. Because the ultimate realizability of deferred tax assets is highly subject to the outcome of future events, the amount established as a valuation allowance is considered to be a significant estimate that is subject to change. To the extent a valuation allowance is established or there is a change in the allowance during a period, the change is reflected with a corresponding increase or decrease in income tax expense in the consolidated statements of operations.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:5PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Stock-Based Compensation&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:5PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	ARI uses the Black-Scholes model to value stock options granted. Expected volatility is based on historical volatility of the Company&#x2019;s stock. The expected life of options granted represents the period of time that options granted are expected to be outstanding. The risk-free rate for periods within the contractual term of the options is based on the U.S. Treasury yields in effect at the time of grant. As stock-based compensation expense recognized in our results of operations is based on awards ultimately expected to vest, the amount has been reduced for estimated forfeitures, which were estimated based on our historical experience
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	ARI values restricted stock issued under its Equity Plans at fair market value on the date of grant.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Occasionally the restrictions of the stock are based on future variables such as market price, and require the more sophisticated Monte Carlo Simulation Model to value the award
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:5PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Common Stock Warrants
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:5PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	ARI may issue common stock warrants in connection with debt and equity financing arrangements. In such instances, the terms of the agreements are assessed to determine whether the instrument qualifies as an equity arrangement or a liability arrangement
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Arrangements determined to be derivatives are recorded at fair value as liabilities on the consolidated balance sheet, with periodic gains and losses related to the change in fair value recorded to earnings on the consolidated statement of operations. The Company had outstanding warrants to purchase
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	178,800
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	shares of common stock at a strike price of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	$2.00
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	per share at July 31, 2016, with an expiration date of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	March 15, 2018
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:5PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Advertising Costs&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:5PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Advertising costs, which are included in sales and marketing expense on the consolidated statements of operations, are expensed as incurred. Total advertising costs were approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	$40,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	$115,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	in fiscal 2016 and fiscal 2015, respectively.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Comprehensive Income
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:5PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Comprehensive income is a more inclusive financial reporting method that includes disclosure of financial information that has not been recognized in the calculation of net income. We reported comprehensive income, which includes net income and foreign currency translation adjustments, in the consolidated statements of comprehensive income and shareholders&#x2019; equity for fiscal 2016 and fiscal 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:5PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Legal Provisions&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:5PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	ARI is periodically involved in legal proceedings arising from contracts, patents or other matters in the normal course of business. We reserve for any material estimated losses if the outcome is probable and reasonably estimable, in accordance with GAAP. We had
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	no
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	legal provisions in fiscal 2016 or fiscal 2015 and management believes that the results of any outstanding litigation will not have a material impact on the Company&#x2019;s financial condition or results of operations.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;PUNCTUATION-WRAP:HANGING;VERTICAL-ALIGN:BASELINE;FONT-FAMILY:CG TIMES (W1);FONT-SIZE: 8PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">

<A NAME="eolPage40"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:5PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Recently Adopted Accounting Standards
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:5PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	On August 1, 2015, the Company retrospectively adopted Accounting Standards Update (&#x201C;ASU&#x201D;) 2015-03 related to the presentation of debt issuance costs. Debt issuance costs of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	$29,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	, previously recorded to prepaid expenses and other, and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	$84,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	, previously recorded to other long-term assets as of July 31, 2015, are now presented as a direct deduction from the carrying amount of long-
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	term debt on the consolidated balance sheet, net of amortization.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:5PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	New Accounting Pronouncements
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:5PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	The FASB has issued ASU No. 2014-09, Revenue from Contracts with Customers: Topic 606, which affects any entity using U.S. GAAP that either enters into contracts with customers to transfer goods or services or enters into contracts for the transfer of nonfinancial assets unless those contracts are within the scope of other guidance. The core principle of this guidance is that an entity should recognize revenue to depict the transfer of promised goods or services to customers in an amount that reflects the consideration to which the entity expects to be entitled in exchange for those goods or services. The amendments in this ASU are effective for annual reporting periods beginning after December 15, 2017, including interim periods within that reporting period. Early application is not permitted. An entity should apply the amendments in this ASU using one of the following two methods: (i) retrospectively to each prior reporting period; or (ii) retrospectively with the cumulative effect of initially applying this ASU recognized at the date of initial application. We are evaluating the potential impact of adopting this standard on the consolidated financial statements for fiscal 2019 and beyond.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:5PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	The FASB recently issued ASU No. 2015-17, Balance sheet classification of deferred taxes:&nbsp;&nbsp;this amendment requires that deferred tax assets and liabilities be classified as noncurrent in the balance sheet
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	The amendments in this ASU are effective for annual reporting periods beginning after December 15, 2016.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The adoption of this guidance will have no impact on our financial position, results of operations or cash flows.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:5PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	Management has reviewed recently issued accounting pronouncements and believes that there are no other pronouncements that will have a material impact on the Company&#x2019;s consolidated financial statements in fiscal 2017.
</FONT>
</P>

</EFX_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Basic and Diluted Net Income per Common Share&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Basic net income per common share is computed by dividing net income by the basic weighted average number of common shares outstanding during the period. Diluted net income per common share is computed by dividing net income by the weighted average number of common shares outstanding during the period and reflects the potential dilution that could occur if all of ARI&#x2019;s outstanding stock options and warrants that are in the money were exercised (calculated usin
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	g the treasury stock method).
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
</P>
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;PUNCTUATION-WRAP:HANGING;VERTICAL-ALIGN:BASELINE;FONT-FAMILY:CG TIMES (W1);FONT-SIZE: 8PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
	40
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>

	The term loan and any loans made under the SVB revolving credit facility accrue interest at a per annum rate equal to the Prime Rate plus the Applicable Margin for Prime Rate Loans set forth in the chart below based on the Total Leverage Ratio, as defined in the Modification Agreement. The Company had

	$0

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	any loans made under the revolving facility is required to be paid in its entirety on or before
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Nov
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	ember 30, 2016.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Principal with respect to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	the term loan is required to be paid in quarterly installments on the first day of each fiscal quarter of the Company as follows:&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	$151,250
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	commenced on November 1, 2014 through August 1, 2016;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	$226,875
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	commencing on November 1, 2016 through August 1, 2017; and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	$302,500
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	commencing on November 1, 2017 through August 1, 2019. All remaining
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	principal with respect to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	the term loan is due and payable on September 30, 2019. The Company is permitted to prepay all of, but not less than all of, the outstanding principal amount of the term loan upon notice to SVB and, in certain circumstances, the payment of a prepayment penalty of up to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	$61,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. Following
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	July 31, 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	, the Modification Agreement requires the Company to make additional payments in the amount of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	25%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	of excess cash flow, as defined in the agreement, until the Company&#x2019;s Total Leverage Ratio is less than
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	2.00
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	to 1.00.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	The Modification Agreement contains covenants that restrict, among other things and subject to certain conditions, the ability of the Company to permit a change of control, incur debt, create liens on its assets, make certain investments, enter into merger or acquisition transactions and make distributions to its shareholders. Financial covenants include the maintenance of a minimum Total Leverage Ratio equal to or less than
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	3.00
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	to 1.00 and the maintenance of a Fixed Charge Coverage Ratio (as defined in the Modification Agreement) equal to or greater than
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	1.25
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	to 1.00.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	The Total Leverage Ratio was
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	1.13
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	and the Fixed Charge Ratio was
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	2.22
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	for the twelve months ended July 31, 2016.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	The Modification Agreement also contains customary events of default that, if triggered, could result in an acceleration of the Company&#x2019;s obligations under the Modification Agreement. The loans are secured by a first priority security interest in substantially all assets of the Company.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	TCS Promissory Notes
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	In connection with the acquisition of TCS, on
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	September 30, 2014
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	, the Company issued
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	two
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	promissory notes (the &#x201C;TCS Notes&#x201D;) in the aggregate principal amount of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	$3,000,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	to the former owners of TCS. In February 2015, the principal amount of the TCS Notes was reduced by
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	$67,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	as a result of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	post-closing adjustments to the valuation of the net assets acquired, pursuant to the terms of the asset purchase agreement.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF;">
	The TCS Notes initially accrue interest on the outstanding unpaid principal balance at a rate per annum equal to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF;">
	5.0%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF;">
	;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF;">
	however, if any amount payable under a TCS Note is not paid when due, such overdue amount will bear interest at the default rate of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF;">
	7.5%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF;">
	from the date of such non-payment until such amount is paid in full. Accrued interest on the TCS Notes is due and payable quarterly commencing on
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF;">
	December 29, 2014
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF;">
	and continuing on each 90th calendar day thereafter, until
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF;">
	September 30, 2018
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF;">
	, at which time all accrued interest and outstanding principal balance will be due and payable in full. The first four payments due and payable under the TCS Notes
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF;">
	were interest-
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF;">
	only payments, and payments of principal and interest commence
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF;">
	d
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF;">
	on December 29, 2015. The payments are subject to acceleration upon certain Events of Default, as defined in the TCS Notes.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	DCi Promissory Note
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	In connection with the acquisition of Direct Communications Inc. (&#x201C;DCi&#x201D;), on
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	July 13, 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	, the Company issued a promissory note (the &#x201C;DCi Note&#x201D;) in the aggregate principal amount of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	$2,000,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	the former owners of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	DCi.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The principal amount of the DCi Note was reduced by approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	$64
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	as a result of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	post-closing adjustments to the estimated valuation of the net assets acquired, pursuant to the terms of the asset purchase agreement.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The DCi
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF;">
	Note initially accrues interest on the outstanding unpaid principal balance at a rate per annum equal to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF;">
	4.0%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF;">
	. Accrued interest on the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	DCi
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF;">
	Note is due and payable quarterly commencing on
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF;">
	October 13, 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF;">
	and continuing on each 90th calendar day thereafter, until
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF;">
	July 13, 2019
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF;">
	, at which time all accrued interest and outstanding principal balance will be due and payable in full. The first four payments due and payable under the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	DCi
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF;">
	Note
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF;">
	we
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF;">
	re interest only payments, and payments of principal and interest commence
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF;">
	d
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF;">
	with
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF;">
	the payment due on October 13, 2016. The payments are subject to acceleration upon certain Events of Default, as defined in the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	DCi
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #FFFFFF;">
	Note.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
</P>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Business Combinations
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	DCi Acquisition
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	On
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	July 13, 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	, the Company acquired substantially all of the assets of DCi, a leading provider of differentiated product content and electronic catalog software serving manufacturers, distributors, jobbers and independent retailers in the AAPS.&nbsp;Consideration
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	for the acquisition included: (i
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	) a cash payment equal to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	$3,750,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	; (ii
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	) &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	159,795
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	shares of th
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	e Company&#x2019;s common stock; and (iii
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	) &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	the issuance of a promissory note in principal amount of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	$1,93
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	(as adjusted)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	the former owners of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	DCi
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	The D
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Ci
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	acquisition
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	was intended
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	to accelerate
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	the Company&#x2019;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	s growth in the AAPS and provide a platform to further expand the reach of ARI&#x2019;s data-driven eCommerce websites and automotive point-of-sale software. The combined customer benefits and operational efficiencies are expected to result in a stronger organization that can create more value for our customers, shareholders and employees.
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	I
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	ntangible assets include the fair value of tradenames, customer relationships, and non-com
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	petition agreements. G
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	oodwill represents the additional benefits provided to the Company by the acquisition of DCi operational synergies. The Company acquired approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	$3,250,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	of tax deductible goodwill related to the DCi acquisition.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	TASCO Acquisition
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	On
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	April 27, 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	, the Company acquired substantially all of the assets of TASCO Corporation&nbsp;and its affiliated company Signal Extraprise Corporation (collectively &#x201C;TASCO&#x201D;), a leading provider of business management software designed exclusively for&nbsp;the ATW industry.&nbsp;Consideration
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	for the acquisition included: (i
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	) a cash payment at the closing of the transaction equal to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	$1,750,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	, which was funded through borrowing on the Company
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	&#x2019;s revolving credit facility; (ii
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	) &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	242,424
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	shares of the Company&#x2019;s comm
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	on stock; and (iii
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	) a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	$138,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	(as adjusted)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	holdback payable on April 27, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	The Company determined that the TASCO assets acquired did not constitute a business that is &#x201C;significant&#x201D; as defined in the applicable SEC regulations.
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	TCS Acquisition
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	On
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	September 30, 2014
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	, the Company acquired substantially all of the assets of TCS, a leading provider of software, websites and digital marketing services designed exclusively for dealers, wholesalers, retreaders and manufacturers within the ATW industries. Consideration for the acquisition included (
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	i
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	) a cash payment equal to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	$4,200,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	; (ii
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	) &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	618,744
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	shares o
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	f the Company's common stock; (iii
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	) the issuance of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	two
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	promissory notes in aggregate principal amount of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	$2,933,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	(as adjusted) to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	the former owners of TCS; and (iv
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	) a contingent earn-out purchase price contingent upon the attainment of specific revenue goals over the first
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	three
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	years following the acquisition.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	The TCS acquisition increased the Company&#x2019;s portfolio of ATW dealer websites by more than
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	30%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. The acquisition is expected to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	continue to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	accelerate ARI&#x2019;s opportunity to drive organic growth through the cross&#x2010;selling of new products. It also provides solutions for the entire ATW supply chain, including wholesalers, retreaders and manufacturers. The TCS business offers a business management solution for ATW dealers as well as for auto repair shops. The combined customer benefits and operational efficiencies are expected to result in a stronger organization that can create more value for our customers, shareholders and employees
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
</P>
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>

	Intangible assets include the fair value of tradenames, customer relationships, and non-competition agreements. Goodwill represents the additional benefits provided to the Company by the acquisition of TCS operational synergies. The Company acquired approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	$5,200,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	of tax deductible goodwill related to the TCS acquisition

	Pro Forma Information

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	The following unaudited pro forma combined financial information presents the Company's results as if the Company had acquired TCS and DCi on August 1, 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. The unaudited pro forma information has been prepared with the following considerations:

<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:0PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:0PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	8
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Capital and Operating Leases&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	The Company leases certain furniture, leasehold improvements and equipment under capital lease arrangements with monthly payment terms ranging from
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	7
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	years and a weighted average interest rate of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	8.8%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. The Company recognized
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	$143,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	$146,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	of depreciation expense related to fixed assets under capital lease agreements during
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	fiscal 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	and 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	, respectively.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
</P>
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;PUNCTUATION-WRAP:HANGING;VERTICAL-ALIGN:BASELINE;FONT-FAMILY:CG TIMES (W1);FONT-SIZE: 8PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">

<HR SIZE="3" STYLE="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<P STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage47"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	The Company leases office space and certain office equipment under operating lease arrangements expiring through 2021.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Annual rent increases under these operating leases range from
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	0%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	5%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	The Company is generally liable for its share of the landlord&#x2019;s direct operating expenses and real estate taxes related to these leases. Total rental and related operating expense for the operating leases was
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	$1,055,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	fiscal 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	$883,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	fiscal 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Leasehold improvements are depreciated over the shorter of their useful life or the term of the lease.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Rent expense for leased offices is recognized on a straight-line basis over the lease terms, which differs from the pattern of payments required by certain leases. Other accrued liabilities included
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	$35,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	$20,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	of deferred rent and other long term liabilities included
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	$166,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	$200,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	of deferred rent at
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	July 31, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	and 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	, respectively, related to these leases
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
