<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	9
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Stock-based Compensation Plans&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	The Company uses the Black-Scholes model to value stock options granted. Volatility is calculated as managements&#x2019; estimate of future volatility over the expected term of the option based on historical volatility of the Company&#x2019;s stock. The expected life of options granted represents the period of time that options granted are expected to be outstanding. The risk-free rate for periods within the contractual term of the options is based on the United States Treasury yields in effect at the time of grant
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Stock options granted to employees under the Company&#x2019;s stock option plan typically vest
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	25%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	on the first anniversary of the grant and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	25%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	on the one-
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	year anniversary of each of the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	three
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	following years. Stock options granted to non-employee directors under the Company&#x2019;s stock option plan typically vest
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	50%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	on the first anniversary of the grant and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	50%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	on the next one-
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	year anniversary
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	The Company recognizes stock option expense over the vesting period for each vesting tranche.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	The
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	re were
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	no
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	options issued in fiscal 2016.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	As recognizing stock-based compensation expense is based on awards ultimately expected to vest, the amount of recognized expense has been reduced for estimated forfeitures
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	10.1%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	based on the Company&#x2019;s historical experience. Total stock compensation expense recognized by the Company related to stock options was approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	$79,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	$152,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	during
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	fiscal 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	fiscal 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	, respectively. There was approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	$38,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	$142,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	of total unrecognized compensation costs related to non-vested options granted under the Company&#x2019;s stock option plans as of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	July 31, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	and 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	, respectively. Total unrecognized compensation cost will be adjusted for the difference between estimated and actual forfeitures. There were
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	no
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	capitalized stock-based compensation costs during the years ended
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	July 31, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	or 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	The Company received approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	$94,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	from the exercise of stock options during fiscal 2016.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	2000 Stock Option Plan&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	The Company&#x2019;s 2000 Stock Option Plan (the &#x201C;2000 Plan&#x201D;) had
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	1,950,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	shares of common stock authorized for issuance. Each incentive stock option that was granted under the 2000 Plan is exercisable for a period of not more than
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	10
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	years from the date of grant (
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	five
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	years in the case of a participant who is a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	10%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	shareholder of the Company, unless the stock options are nonqualified), or such shorter period as determined by the Compensation Committee, and shall lapse upon the expiration of said period, or earlier upon termination of the participant&#x2019;s employment with the Company. The 2000 Plan expired on December 13, 2010, at which time it was terminated except for outstanding options. While options previously granted under the 2000 Plan will remain outstanding through the remainder of their terms, or until exercised, no new options may be granted under the 2000 Plan. Changes in option shares under the 2000 Plan during
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	fiscal 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	were as follows:
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE;WIDTH: 100.00%;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;">
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM" STYLE="WIDTH:38.78%;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-LEFT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-RIGHT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #AUTO;HEIGHT:1.00PT;PADDING:0PT;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;HEIGHT:1.00PT;OVERFLOW:HIDDEN;FONT-SIZE: 1PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:1PT;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM" STYLE="WIDTH:01.14%;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-LEFT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-RIGHT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BACKGROUND-COLOR: #AUTO;HEIGHT:1.00PT;PADDING:0PT;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:9PT;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	2010 Equity Incentive Plan&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	The Board of Directors adopted the ARI Network Services, Inc. 2010 Equity Incentive Plan (as amended, the &#x201C;2010 Plan&#x201D;) on November 9, 2010. The plan was approved by the Company's shareholders in December 2010, and amendments to the 2010 Plan were approved by the Company&#x2019;s shareholders in January 2014. The 2010 Plan is the successor to the Company&#x2019;s 2000 Plan. There are
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	1,850,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	shares of Company common stock authorized for issuance under the 2010 Plan.&nbsp;Potential awards under the 2010 Plan include incentive stock options and non-statutory stock options, shares of restricted stock or restricted stock units, stock appreciation rights
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	(&#x201C;SARs&#x201D;)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	, and shares of common stock
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Up to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	1,525,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	of the shares authorized for issuance under the 2010 Plan may be used for common stock, restricted stock or restricted stock unit awards.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	The exercise price for options and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	SAR
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	s under the 2010 Plan cannot be less than
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	100%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	of the fair market value of the Company&#x2019;s common stock on the date of grant, and the exercise prices for options and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	SARs
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	cannot be repriced without shareholder approval, except to reflect changes to the capital structure of the Company as described in the 2010 Plan. The maximum term of options and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	SAR
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	s under the 2010 Plan is
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	10
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	years. The 2010 Plan does not have lib
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	eral share counting provisions,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	such as provisions that would permit shares withheld for payment of taxes or the exercise price of stock options to be re-granted under the plan.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Employee Stock Purchase Plan&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	The Company&#x2019;s 2000 Employee Stock Purchase Plan, as amended, (&#x201C;ESPP&#x201D;) has
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	575,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	shares of common stock reserved for issuance, of which
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	300,280
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	263,974
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	of the shares have been issued as of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	July 31, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	and 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	, respectively. All employees with at least
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	six
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	months of service are eligible to participate. Shares may be purchased at the end of a specified period at the lower of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	85%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	of the market value at the beginning or end of the specified period through accumulation of payroll deductions, not to exceed
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	5,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	shares per employee per year. The Company expensed
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	$39,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	$31,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	related to the ESPP discount during
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	fiscal 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	and 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	, respectively.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Restricted Stock
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Pursuant to the 2010 Plan, there are 1,525,000 shares authorized for issuance in the form of shares of common stock, restricted stock or restricted stock units. The Company grants restricted stock to its directors as an annual retainer, its officers under the Long Term Equity Bonus Plan (&#x201C;LTEB&#x201D;) and from time to time to directors, officers or employees as incentive compensation or, in some cases, as discretionary compensation in place of cash. The Company recognized compensation expense of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	$310,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	$263,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	during
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	fiscal 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	fiscal 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	, respectively, related to restricted stock expensed over the vesting period.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	The remaining balance of unrecognized compensation expense related to restricted stock was
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	$383,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	at
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	July 31, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	.

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">

	risk-
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	free interest rate, and is expensed over the vesting period. The remaining balance of unrecognized compensation expense related to the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;COLOR:#000000;">
	fiscal 2016

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	&#xFEFF;
</FONT>

</EFX_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	The provision for income taxes is based on taxes payable under currently enacted tax laws and an analysis of temporary differences between the book and tax bases of the Company&#x2019;s assets and liabilities, including various accruals, allowances, depreciation and amortization, and does not represent current taxes due. The tax effect of these temporary differences and the estimated benefit from tax net operating losses are reported as deferred tax assets and liabilities in the consolidated balance sheets. We have unused net operating loss carry forwards ("NOLs") for federal income tax purposes, and as a result, we generally only incur alternative minimum taxes at the federal level that are currently payable.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	A reconciliation between income tax expense and income taxes computed by applying the statutory federal income tax rate of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	34%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	and the state rate of approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	3%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	to U.S. based income (loss) before income taxes for the year ended July 31 is as follows (in thousands):&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:6PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	In March 2015, the Wisconsin legislature enacted a change for tax years beginning on or after January 1, 2014 to extend the carryforward period for corporate NOLs from
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	15
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	20
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	years. As a result of this change, the Company recorded additional deferred tax assets of approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	$466,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	with an off-setting valuation allowance of approximately $420,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	An assessment is performed
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	periodically
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	of the likelihood that the Company&#x2019;s net deferred tax assets will be realized from future taxable income. To the extent management believes it is more likely than not that some portion, or all, of the deferred tax asset will not be realized, a valuation allowance is established. This assessment is based on all available evidence, both positive and negative, in evaluating the likelihood of realizability. Issues considered in the assessment include future reversals of existing taxable temporary differences, estimates of future taxable income (exclusive of reversing temporary differences and carryforwards) and prudent tax planning strategies available in future periods. Because the ultimate realizability of deferred tax assets is highly subject to the outcome of future events, the amount established as a valuation allowance is considered to be a significant estimate that is subject to change in the near term. To the extent a valuation allowance is established or there is a change in the allowance during a period, the change is reflected with a corresponding increase or decrease in the tax provision in the consolidated statements of operations
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	The Company recorded expense related to a net change in estimate on our valuation allowance related to US deferred tax assets of approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	$420,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	, or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	$0.03
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	per basic and diluted share related to estimated expiration of the deferred tax assets resulting from the extension of NOL carryforward expirations during
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	fiscal 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	as a result of our evaluation of the likelihood that our net deferred tax assets will be realized from future taxable income.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	There was no change in the remaining estimated valuation allowance during fiscal 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	The Company has NOLs related to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	tax losses incurred by its Netherlands operation
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Under tax laws in the Netherlands, NOLs are able to be carried forward for a period of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	nine
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	years. The Company has determined that, consistent with prior periods, it is not likely that the net operating losses will be utilized by the Company. This conclusion was primarily based on the negative evidence of a history of losses and expired NOLs related to this entity. In the opinion of the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	C
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	ompany, there is not enough positive evidence to overcome this negative evidence. Therefore, a full valuation allowance of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	$430,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	$508,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	are recorded, resulting in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	$0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	net deferred tax assets related to the Netherlands operation at
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	July 31, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	and 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	, respectively
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	The Company also has
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	an
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	NOL related to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	a current year
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	tax loss
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	incurred by its
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	India
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	operation
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	Under tax laws in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	India
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	, NOLs are able to be carried forward for a period of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	eight
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	years. The Company has determined that it is not likely that the net operating loss
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	will be utilized by the Company primarily based on the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	start-up nature of this operation
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. Therefore, a full valuation allowance of
</FONT>
</P>
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;PUNCTUATION-WRAP:HANGING;VERTICAL-ALIGN:BASELINE;FONT-FAMILY:CG TIMES (W1);FONT-SIZE: 8PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	We perform an evaluation of uncertain tax positions as a component of income tax expense on an annual basis. We determined that the Company did not have any significant risk related to income tax expense and therefore
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	no
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	amounts were reserved for uncertain tax positions as of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	July 31, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	and 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	. We will accrue and recognize interest and penalties related to uncertain tax positions as a component of income tax expense if it becomes necessary. Fiscal years subsequent to 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	remain open and subject to examination by state tax jurisdictions and the United States federal tax authorities.
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	11
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Employee Benefit Plan&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	ARI has a qualified retirement savings plan (the &#x201C;401(k) Plan&#x201D;) covering its employees. Each employee may elect to reduce his or her current compensation by up to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	50%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	, up to a maximum of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	$18,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	&nbsp;(
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	$24,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	over age 50) in calendar year
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	and 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	(subject to adjustment in future years) and have the amount of the reduction contributed to the 401(k) Plan. Company contributions to the 401(k) Plan are at the discretion of the Board of Directors. The Company contributes
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	$0.50
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	per $1.00 contributed by the employees with a maximum of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	4%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	of an employee&#x2019;s salary. The Company contributed
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	$
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	$2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	8,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	to the 401(k) Plan related to matching of employee contributions during
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	fiscal 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">
	and 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;">

</FONT>

	from the sale, after deducting underwriting discounts and commissions and estimated offering expenses payable by the Company.

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:9PT;">
	FY
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:9PT;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 10PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;FONT-SIZE: 9PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:9PT;">
	The Management Incentive Bonus Plan (&#x201C;MIBP&#x201D;) is the executive bonus plan for all executives. The plan includes two key performance targets for ARI, Adjusted EBITDA and Recurring Revenue (&#x201C;RR&#x201D;), each worth 50% of the total on target bonus potential.&nbsp;&nbsp;Based on the company&#x2019;s performance in those two areas, the following Grids dictate the ultimate payout of the MBO bonus as a percentage:
</FONT>
